gomodel:SYNGO_868  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Paper uses a pharmacological description to suggest that P2X7 receptor neurohypophysial nerve terminals regulates dense core vesicle release. A P2X7 antibody characterized by selective immunoprecipitation is used in immunocytochemistry of isolated selectively labels to identify co-localization with the released neuropeptide Arginine vasopressin.\n\n27/10/2017 Pim\n- Authors use P2X7R-selective agonists and antagonist.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods: All studies were performed using rat brain tissue..........." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-27" ;
